column5: Nice set up.
Hmmm January Hmm wuthca gonna do all summer with a new Truck and Boat Hmm
Sweet Ride Stoty.
Ha ha ha, too bad my EI runs out end of June!
Nice set up Stoty.  Good luck with the job hunting and/or career change.
Here is my rig for the next little while!  2005 Chevy Avalanche - Fully loaded 2006 Ranger 175vs - Fully loaded       If any fellow OFC'ers see me, please be sure to come say hi!  *Stoty
Say Hi? Don't be surprised if you walk out of your house and find me sitting in the passenger seat of your ranger one morning.
:lol:      NICE SET UP!!!  since kickingfrog is already in the front I'd gladly sit in the back!!  CONGRATS!!!  RFS
Ah, got a bigger truck did you, looks like a great match for that beauty of a boat you have!   Great set up man, can't wait to see some big lake reports from you this year!  Mike
Must have a good paying job too.
Nice rig! Now you need to upgrade the drive way.
Nice rig dude. Are you fishing tournaments this year, why the sponsors?
Looks like you had to sell your house to pay for it though....Was it worth it???
Don't have to worry about those pesky boat ramps any more now eh  Nice ride...you will love it.  Now go get that truck dirty and that boat wet
Real beauty Stoty     Congratulations I'm sure you'll have many hours of happiness with this setup. Leechman
Uhhhhhhh, your hanging over onto the road.  Gonna get a ticket for that  Sweet rides bud.  Congrats you to.     Now go get some BIG fish will ya  Joey
That is definitely a gas guzzling combination
drooooooool!  nice set up!
Hey Big Spender lol.  sweet
Don't laugh he'll do it
Well, glad to see the recession isn't affecting everyone!  Great rides Stoty!
Now that's sweet.
Excellent set up! I dont see the OFC sticker on truck or boat!
What is really nice is when I remember some of your posts about a year ago this time, Things seem to have really turned around for you. Good on you!

Yes, I am doing tournaments this year! Probably going to do the whole Bassmaina circuit and BM100 circuit!   Yes, they sure have. So far 2009 has brought me a new: (in no particular order, lol)  - boat - truck - woman - house  It's about time that I can admit that I am finally "happy".    Thanks everyone for the nice words! Much appreciated.
nice pics, again.......still looking good!.....you must have found work too.  good luck in the tourny's bro.  RR

Actually...got screwed over by a local company here in Port Hope again! He used me for 2 projects he needed to get done, then boom...got the boot!  So, I'm back to looking for something yet again!  I think I am going to go back to school actually, for Firefighting in January though. A nice STABLE career!
sick!

Nice combo stoty.  Know a couple people with avys and they are awesome on gas when towing a rig.  Enjoy it and the BM115s, some really good sticks in that circuit and you will have a great time and learn a lot!
Dude, you need a  bigger driveway lol
